Miscellaneous Highlights: San Antonio Spurs won against Portland Trail Blazers with a score of 118-105.
The Spurs improved to 4-5 in their first nine games.
Others: Victor Wembanyama finished with 12 points, eight rebounds, two assists, four steals, and three blocks while shooting 4/13 from the field in 32 minutes.
NBA fans reacted negatively to Wembanyama's performance, citing issues with his shooting and rebounding.
The Spurs will play their next game on Saturday evening against the Utah Jazz.
